auto_merge.commit_message:
See https://groups.google.com/g/cython-users/c/JUuzNBAppzQ
    
This allows them to be linked together without the C++ compiler
complaining (because it doesn't treat them as individual per-translation
unit). It won't work in C, but I also believe it isn't necessary in C.
    
These are the two main structs I know of that almost always have
different definitions for each module. It may well be worth doing some
of the other utility code ones too because they *can* if you end up
mixing compilation options. But usually they should be the same so it's
lower priority.

commit.message:
Add anonymous namespace to per-module structs

See https://groups.google.com/g/cython-users/c/JUuzNBAppzQ

This allows them to be linked together without the C++ compiler
complaining (because it doesn't treat them as individual
per-translation unit).  It won't work in C, but I also believe
it isn't necessary in C.

These are the two main structs I know of that almost always have
different definitions for each module. It may well be worth doing
some of the other utility code ones too because they *can* if
you end up mixing compilation options. But usually they should
be the same so it's lower priority.
